{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1778546809145,"sessionID":"ses_1e65d1530ffeDUY9bNFKPZlPsk","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"bash","callID":"chatcmpl-tool-b635fd70d067d6ac","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"command":"obo-grep.pl -r 'relationship: connecting_branch_of' src/ontology/uberon-edit.obo","description":"Check if 'connecting_branch_of' is used in the ontology with the correct flag."},"output":"...output truncated...\n\nFull output saved to: /home/runner/.local/share/opencode/tool-output/tool_e19a69929001ai76mGQF2cOHCN\n\nxref: FMA:18835\nxref: SCTID:244309002\nxref: Wikipedia:Internal_pudendal_artery\nis_a: UBERON:0007312 ! pudendal artery\nrelationship: connecting_branch_of UBERON:0001309 ! internal iliac artery\nrelationship: in_lateral_side_of UBERON:0006867 {source=\"FMA-abduced-lr\"} ! anal part of perineum\nrelationship: part_of UBERON:0006867 ! anal part of perineum\nrelationship: vessel_supplies_blood_to UBERON:0004176 ! external genitalia\nproperty_value: depiction \"http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/3/3a/Gray1244.png\" xsd:anyURI\n\n[Term]\nid: UBERON:0007316\nname: deep external pudendal artery\ndef: \"The deep external pudendal artery (deep external pudic artery), more deeply seated than the superficial external pudendal artery, passes medialward across the Pectineus and the Adductor longus muscles; it is covered by the fascia lata, which it pierces at the medial side of the thigh, and is distributed, in the male, to the integument of the scrotum and perineum, in the female to the labium majus; its branches anastomose with the scrotal (or labial) branches of the perineal artery.\" [Wikipedia:Deep_external_pudendal_artery]\nsynonym: \"arteria pudenda externa profunda\" EXACT OMO:0003011 [Wikipedia:Deep_external_pudendal_artery]\nsynonym: \"arteriae pudendae externa profunda\" EXACT OMO:0003011 [doi:10.1002/ca.23705]\nsynonym: \"arteriae pudendales externa profunda\" EXACT OMO:0003011 [doi:10.1002/ca.23705]\nxref: FMA:20739\nxref: SCTID:31708008\nxref: Wikipedia:Deep_external_pudendal_artery\nintersection_of: UBERON:0013137 ! external pudendal artery\nintersection_of: part_of UBERON:0035551 ! deep vasculature\nrelationship: connecting_branch_of UBERON:0002060 {source=\"FMA\"} ! femoral artery\nrelationship: part_of UBERON:0001308 {source=\"FMA\"} ! external iliac artery\nrelationship: part_of UBERON:0002060 {source=\"FMA\"} ! femoral artery\nrelationship: vessel_supplies_blood_to UBERON:0004176 ! external genitalia\nproperty_value: depiction \"http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/4/43/Gray549.png\" xsd:anyURI\n\n[Term]\nid: UBERON:0007317\nname: superficial external pudendal artery\ndef: \"An artery that arises from the medial side of the femoral artery, close to the superficial epigastric artery and superficial iliac circumflex artery.\" [Wikipedia:Superficial_external_pudendal_artery]\ncomment: After piercing the femoral sheath and fascia cribrosa, it courses medialward, across the spermatic cord (or round ligament in the female), to be distributed to the integument on the lower part of the abdomen, the penis and scrotum in the male, and the labium majus in the female, anastomosing with branches of the internal pudendal artery. it crosses superficial to the inguinal ligament[WP]\nsynonym: \"arteria pudenda externa superficialis\" RELATED OMO:0003011 [Wikipedia:Superficial_external_pudendal_artery]\nsynonym: \"arteriae pudendae externa superficialis\" EXACT OMO:0003011 [doi:10.1002/ca.23705]\nsynonym: \"arteriae pudendales externa superficialis\" EXACT OMO:0003011 [doi:10.1002/ca.23705]\nsynonym: \"superficial external pudic artery\" EXACT []\nxref: FMA:20738\nxref: SCTID:47954000\nxref: Wikipedia:Superficial_external_pudendal_artery\nintersection_of: UBERON:0013137 ! external pudendal artery\nintersection_of: part_of UBERON:0035549 ! vasculature of integument\nrelationship: connecting_branch_of UBERON:0002060 {source=\"FMA\"} ! femoral artery\nrelationship: part_of UBERON:0001308 {source=\"FMA\"} ! external iliac artery\nrelationship: vessel_supplies_blood_to UBERON:0004176 ! external genitalia\nproperty_value: depiction \"http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/4/43/Gray549.png\" xsd:anyURI\n\n[Term]\nid: UBERON:0007610\nname: tibial artery\ndef: \"The anterior and posterior arteries created at the bifurcation of the popliteal artery. The anterior tibial artery begins at the lower border of the popliteus muscle and lies along the tibia at the distal part of the leg to surface superficially anterior to the ankle joint. Its branches are distributed throughout the leg, ankle, and pes. The posterior tibial artery begins at the lower border of the popliteus muscle, lies behind the tibia in the lower part of its course, and is found situated between the medial malleolus and the medial process of the calcaneal tuberosity. Its branches are distributed throughout the leg and foot.\" [MESH:A07.231.114.895]\nxref: EMAPA:36530\nxref: GAID:514\nxref: MA:0002067\nxref: MESH:D016909\nxref: NCIT:C12824\nxref: SCTID:181351007\nxref: UMLS:C0085427 {source=\"ncithesaurus:Tibial_Artery\"}\nis_a: UBERON:0001637 {source=\"MESH\"} ! artery\nrelationship: connecting_branch_of UBERON:0002250 ! popliteal artery\nrelationship: part_of UBERON:0002103 ! hindlimb\n\n[Term]\nid: UBERON:0007693\nname: caroticotympanic artery\ndef: \"The caroticotympanic branch (tympanic branch) is small; it enters the tympanic cavity through a minute foramen in the carotid canal, and anastomoses with the anterior tympanic branch of the internal maxillary, and with the stylomastoid artery.\" [Wikipedia:Caroticotympanic_arteries]\nsynonym: \"arteriae caroticotympanicae\" RELATED OMO:0003011 [Wikipedia:Caroticotympanic_arteries]\nsynonym: \"caroticotympanic branch\" RELATED [Wikipedia:Caroticotympanic_arteries]\nsynonym: \"ramus caroticotympanicus\" RELATED OMO:0003011 [Wikipedia:Caroticotympanic_arteries]\nxref: FMA:49828\nxref: SCTID:148470005\nxref: Wikipedia:Caroticotympanic_arteries\nis_a: UBERON:0001637 ! artery\nrelationship: connecting_branch_of UBERON:0001532 {source=\"FMA\"} ! internal carotid artery\nrelationship: develops_from UBERON:0005608 {source=\"http://www.ajnr.org/cgi/content/full/21/3/572\"} ! hyoid artery\n\n[Term]\nid: UBERON:0008311\nname: penile bulb artery\ndef: \"A short vessel of large caliber which arises from the internal pudendal between the two layers of fascia of the urogenital diaphragm; it passes medialward, pierces the inferior fascia of the urogenital diaphragm, and gives off branches which ramify in the bulb of the urethra and in the posterior part of the corpus spongiosum. It gives off a small branch to the bulbo-urethral gland.\" [Wikipedia:Bulbourethral_artery]\nsynonym: \"arteria bulbi penis\" EXACT [BTO:0005087]\nsynonym: \"artery of bulb of penis\" EXACT [FMA:20864]\nsynonym: \"bulbourethral artery\" RELATED [BTO:0005087]\nxref: BTO:0005087\nxref: FMA:20864\nxref: SCTID:293338009\nxref: Wikipedia:Bulbourethral_artery\nintersection_of: UBERON:0001637 ! artery\nintersection_of: vessel_supplies_blood_to UBERON:0013128 ! bulb of penis\nrelationship: connecting_branch_of UBERON:0007315 {source=\"FMA\"} ! internal pudendal artery\nrelationship: part_of UBERON:0000989 {source=\"Obol\"} ! penis\nrelationship: part_of UBERON:0008320 {source=\"BTO\"} ! common penile artery\n\n[Term]\nid: UBERON:0008321\nname: deep artery of penis\ndef: \"The deep artery of the penis (artery to the corpus cavernosum), one of the terminal branches of the internal pudendal, arises from that vessel while it is situated between the two fascia of the urogenital diaphragm (deep perineal pouch). It pierces the inferior fascia, and, entering the crus penis obliquely, runs forward in the center of the corpus cavernosum penis, to which its branches are distributed.\" [Wikipedia:Deep_artery_of_the_penis]\nsynonym: \"arteria cavernosa penis\" RELATED [BTO:0005086]\nsynonym: \"arteria profunda penis\" EXACT [BTO:0005086]\nsynonym: \"arteria profunda penis\" RELATED OMO:0003011 [Wikipedia:Deep_artery_of_the_penis]\nsynonym: \"cavernosal artery\" RELATED [BTO:0005086]\nsynonym: \"deep penile artery\" EXACT [FMA:19794]\nxref: BTO:0005086\nxref: FMA:19794\nxref: SCTID:244293007\nxref: Wikipedia:Deep_artery_of_the_penis\nintersection_of: UBERON:0001637 ! artery\nintersection_of: part_of UBERON:0035551 ! deep vasculature\nintersection_of: vessel_supplies_blood_to UBERON:0004713 ! corpus cavernosum penis\nrelationship: connecting_branch_of UBERON:0007315 {source=\"FMA\"} ! internal pudendal artery\nrelationship: part_of UBERON:0000989 {source=\"FMA\"} ! penis\nrelationship: part_of UBERON:0008320 {source=\"BTO\"} ! common penile artery\nproperty_value: depiction \"http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/2/2b/Gray543.png\" xsd:anyURI\n\n[Term]\nid: UBERON:0008322\nname: deep artery of clitoris\ndef: \"The deep artery of clitoris is a branch of the internal pudendal artery.\" [Wikipedia:Deep_artery_of_clitoris]\nsynonym: \"arteria profunda clitoridis\" RELATED OMO:0003011 [Wikipedia:Deep_artery_of_clitoris]\nxref: FMA:20870\nxref: SCTID:244297008\nxref: Wikipedia:Deep_artery_of_clitoris\nintersection_of: UBERON:0001637 ! artery\nintersection_of: part_of UBERON:0035551 ! deep vasculature\nintersection_of: vessel_supplies_blood_to UBERON:0006608 ! corpus cavernosum clitoridis\nrelationship: connecting_branch_of UBERON:0007315 {source=\"FMA\"} ! internal pudendal artery\nrelationship: part_of UBERON:0002411 {source=\"FMA\"} ! clitoris\n\n[Term]\nid: UBERON:0008323\nname: dorsal artery of clitoris\ndef: \"The dorsal artery of clitoris is a branch of the internal pudendal artery.\" [Wikipedia:Dorsal_artery_of_clitoris]\nxref: FMA:20867\nxref: SCTID:244298003\nxref: Wikipedia:Dorsal_artery_of_clitoris\nis_a: UBERON:0001637 {source=\"MA\"} ! artery\nrelationship: connecting_branch_of UBERON:0007315 {source=\"FMA\"} ! internal pudendal artery\nrelationship: part_of UBERON:0002411 {source=\"FMA\"} ! clitoris\n\n[Term]\nid: UBERON:0009040\nname: deep circumflex iliac artery\ndef: \"The deep circumflex iliac artery (or deep iliac circumflex artery) is an artery in the pelvis that travels along the iliac crest of the pelvic bone.\" [Wikipedia:Deep_circumflex_iliac_artery]\nsynonym: \"arteria circumflexa ilium profunda\" EXACT [Wikipedia:Deep_circumflex_iliac_artery]\nsynonym: \"arteria circumflexa ilium profunda\" RELATED OMO:0003011 [Wikipedia:Deep_circumflex_iliac_artery]\nsynonym: \"deep iliac circumflex\" RELATED [Wikipedia:Deep_circumflex_iliac_artery]\nsynonym: \"deep iliac circumflex artery\" RELATED [Wikipedia:Deep_circumflex_iliac_artery]\nxref: FMA:20687\nxref: NCIT:C32432\nxref: SCTID:181353005\nxref: UMLS:C0226405 {source=\"ncithesaurus:Deep_Circumflex_Iliac_Artery\"}\nxref: Wikipedia:Deep_circumflex_iliac_artery\nintersection_of: UBERON:0009026 ! iliac circumflex artery\nintersection_of: part_of UBERON:0035551 ! deep vasculature\nrelationship: connecting_branch_of UBERON:0001308 {source=\"FMA\"} ! external iliac artery\nrelationship: part_of UBERON:0001308 {source=\"FMA\"} ! external iliac artery\nproperty_value: depiction \"http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/0/07/Gray586.png\" xsd:anyURI\nproperty_value: depiction \"http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/7/74/Gray586.png\" xsd:anyURI\n\n[Term]\nid: UBERON:0009041\nname: superficial circumflex iliac artery\ndef: \"The superficial iliac circumflex artery (or superficial circumflex iliac), the smallest of the cutaneous branches of the femoral artery, arises close to the superficial epigastric artery, and, piercing the fascia lata, runs lateralward, parallel with the inguinal ligament, as far as the crest of the ilium. It divides into branches which supply the integument of the groin, the superficial fascia, and the superficial subinguinal lymph glands, anastomosing with the deep iliac circumflex, the superior gluteal and lateral femoral circumflex arteries.\" [Wikipedia:Superficial_circumflex_iliac_artery]\nsynonym: \"arteria circumflexa ilium superficialis\" EXACT [Wikipedia:Superficial_iliac_circumflex_artery]\nsynonym: \"iliac circumflex artery\" RELATED [Wikipedia:Superficial_iliac_circumflex_artery]\nsynonym: \"superficial circumflex iliac artery\" RELATED [Wikipedia:Superficial_iliac_circumflex_artery]\nxref: FMA:20737\nxref: NCIT:C52864\nxref: UMLS:C0738891 {source=\"ncithesaurus:Superficial_Circumflex_Iliac_Artery\"}\nxref: Wikipedia:Superficial_circumflex_iliac_artery\nintersection_of: UBERON:0009026 ! iliac circumflex artery\nintersection_of: part_of UBERON:0035549 ! vasculature of integument\nrelationship: connecting_branch_of UBERON:0002060 {source=\"FMA\"} ! femoral artery\nproperty_value: depiction \"http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/8/8b/Gray548.png\" xsd:anyURI\n\n[Term]\nid: UBERON:0009654\nname: alveolar artery\ndef: \"A branch of the maxillary artery that is found in the gingiva, premolars, and molars.\" [ncithesaurus:Alveolar_Artery]\nxref: EMAPA:37069 {source=\"MA:th\"}\nxref: MA:0001913\nxref: NCIT:C52848\nxref: UMLS:C1706783 {source=\"ncithesaurus:Alveolar_Artery\"}\nis_a: UBERON:0001637 {source=\"MA\"} ! artery\nrelationship: connecting_branch_of UBERON:0001616 ! maxillary artery\nrelationship: part_of UBERON:0011595 ! jaw region\nproperty_value: editor_note \"add child terms\" xsd:string\n\n[Term]\nid: UBERON:0009688\nname: posterior inferior cerebellar artery\ndef: \"The posterior inferior cerebellar artery (PICA), the largest branch of the vertebral, is one of the three main arterial blood supplies for the cerebellum.\" [Wikipedia:Posterior_inferior_cerebellar_artery]\nsynonym: \"posterior inferior cerebellar artery\" EXACT [EHDAA2:0000660]\nxref: EHDAA2:0000660\nxref: FMA:50518\nxref: NCIT:C33362\nxref: SCTID:244212001\nxref: UMLS:C0149573 {source=\"ncithesaurus:Posterior_Inferior_Cerebellar_Artery\"}\nxref: Wikipedia:Posterior_inferior_cerebellar_artery\nis_a: UBERON:0001637 {source=\"EHDAA2\"} ! artery\ndisjoint_from: UBERON:0009689 {source=\"lexical\"} ! anterior inferior cerebellar artery\nrelationship: connecting_branch_of UBERON:0001535 {source=\"FMA\"} ! vertebral artery\nrelationship: develops_from UBERON:0001535 {source=\"EHDAA2\"} ! vertebral artery\nrelationship: part_of UBERON:0001535 {source=\"FMA\"} ! vertebral artery\n\n[Term]\nid: UBERON:0009689\nname: anterior inferior cerebellar artery\ndef: \"A basilar artery branch that supplies the anterior portion of the inferior surface of the cerebellum.\" [ncithesaurus:Anterior_Inferior_Cerebellar_Artery]\nxref: EHDAA2:0000587\nxref: EMAPA:37070 {source=\"MA:th\"}\nxref: FMA:50544\nxref: NCIT:C32091\nxref: SCTID:244213006\nxref: UMLS:C0226245 {source=\"ncithesaurus:Anterior_Inferior_Cerebellar_Artery\"}\nxref: Wikipedia:Anterior_inferior_cerebellar_artery\nis_a: UBERON:0003472 ! cerebellar artery\nrelationship: connecting_branch_of UBERON:0001633 {source=\"FMA\"} ! basilar artery\nrelationship: develops_from UBERON:0001532 {source=\"EHDAA2\"} ! internal carotid artery\n\n[Term]\nid: UBERON:0010132\nname: gastroduodenal artery\ndef: \"A small blood vessel in the abdomen that supplies blood directly to the pylorus (distal part of the stomach) and proximal part of the duodenum, and indirectly to the pancreatic head (via the anterior and posterior superior pancreaticoduodenal arteries).\" [Wikipedia:Gastroduodenal_artery]\nsynonym: \"arteria gastroduodenalis\" RELATED OMO:0003011 [Wikipedia:Gastroduodenal_artery]\nxref: EHDAA2:0000310\nxref: EHDAA:8574\nxref: FMA:14775\nxref: galen:GastroduodenalArtery\nxref: SCTID:244269002\nxref: Wikipedia:Gastroduodenal_artery\nis_a: UBERON:0001637 ! artery\nrelationship: connecting_branch_of UBERON:0005436 {source=\"FMA\"} ! common hepatic artery\nrelationship: develops_from UBERON:0005436 {source=\"EHDAA2\"} ! common hepatic artery\nproperty_value: depiction \"http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/6/65/Gray532.png\" xsd:anyURI\n\n[Term]\nid: UBERON:0010250\nname: middle meningeal artery\ndef: \"The middle meningeal artery is typically the third branch of the first part (retromandibular part) of the maxillary artery; one of the two terminal branches of the external carotid artery. After branching off the maxillary artery in the infratemporal fossa, it runs through the foramen spinosum to supply the dura mater and the calvaria. The middle meningeal artery is the largest of the three (paired) arteries which supply the meninges, the others being the anterior meningeal artery and the posterior meningeal artery. In approximately half of subjects it branches into an accessory meningeal artery. The middle meningeal artery runs beneath the pterion. It is vulnerable to injury at this point, where the skull is thin. Rupture of the artery may give rise to an epidural hematoma.\" [Wikipedia:Middle_meningeal_artery]\nsynonym: \"arteria meningea media\" RELATED OMO:0003011 [Wikipedia:Middle_meningeal_artery]\nxref: FMA:49711\nxref: SCTID:278100005\nxref: Wikipedia:Middle_meningeal_artery\nis_a: UBERON:0003474 ! meningeal artery\nrelationship: connecting_branch_of UBERON:0001616 {source=\"FMA\"} ! maxillary artery\nproperty_value: depiction \"http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/1/1e/Middle_meningeal_artery.png\" xsd:anyURI\n\n[Term]\nid: UBERON:0010251\nname: anterior meningeal artery\ndef: \"A meningeal branch to the dura mater arising from the anterior ethmoidal artery.\" [Wikipedia:Anterior_ethmoidal_artery#Branches]\nsynonym: \"a. ethmoidalis anterior\" RELATED OMO:0003011 [Wikipedia:Anterior_ethmoidal_artery]\nsynonym: \"anterior ethmoid arteries\" RELATED [Wikipedia:Anterior_ethmoidal_artery]\nsynonym: \"anterior ethmoid artery\" RELATED [Wikipedia:Anterior_ethmoidal_artery]\nsynonym: \"anterior meningeal arteries\" RELATED [Wikipedia:Anterior_ethmoidal_artery]\nsynonym: \"anterior meningeal artery\" RELATED [Wikipedia:Anterior_ethmoidal_artery]\nsynonym: \"anterior meningeal branch of anterior ethmoidal artery\" EXACT [FMA:49993]\nsynonym: \"arteria ethmoidalis anterior\" RELATED OMO:0003011 [Wikipedia:Anterior_ethmoidal_artery]\nsynonym: \"ramus meningeus anterior (arteria ethmoidalis anterioris)\" EXACT OMO:0003011 [FMA:49993, FMA:TA]\nxref: FMA:49993\nxref: NCIT:C32099\nxref: SCTID:369327009\nxref: UMLS:C0226187 {source=\"ncithesaurus:Anterior_Meningeal_Artery\"}\nxref: Wikipedia:Anterior_ethmoidal_artery#Branches\nis_a: UBERON:0003474 ! meningeal artery\nrelationship: connecting_branch_of UBERON:0012318 {source=\"Wikipedia\"} ! anterior ethmoidal artery\nproperty_value: depiction \"http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/c/ce/Gray514.png\" xsd:anyURI\nproperty_value: editor_note \"this needs checking as part of a general revision of the blood vessels and their branches - unclear if the anterior meningeal artery should be treated separately from the anterior ethmoidal artery (ie as a branch) or the same thing\" xsd:string\n\n[Term]\nid: UBERON:0010399\nname: spleen trabecular artery\ndef: \"One of the branches of the splenic artery[MP].\" [MP:0002354, Wikipedia:Trabecular_arteries]\nsubset: pheno_slim\nsynonym: \"trabecular artery\" RELATED []\nxref: MA:0000759\nxref: NCIT:C49775\nxref: UMLS:C1710159 {source=\"ncithesaurus:Splenic_Trabecular_Artery\"}\nxref: Wikipedia:Trabecular_arteries\nintersection_of: UBERON:0001637 ! artery\nintersection_of: part_of UBERON:0001265 ! trabecula of spleen\nrelationship: connecting_branch_of UBERON:0001194 {source=\"MP\"} ! splenic artery\nrelationship: contributes_to_morphology_of UBERON:0002106 ! spleen\nproperty_value: external_definition \"When the splenic artery passes into the trabecula of the spleen and branches, they become known as the trabecular arteries. When these arteries then reach the white pulp, and become covered with Periarteriolar lymphoid sheaths, the name changes again to central arteries (or central arterioles). Branches of the central arteries are given to the red pulp, and these are called penicillar arteries).[Wikipedia]\" xsd:string {ontology=\"Wikipedia\", source=\"Wikipedia:Trabecular_arteries\"}\n\n[Term]\nid: UBERON:0010401\nname: spleen central arteriole\ndef: \"A blood vessel surrounded by the periarteriolar lymphoid sheath that connects the trabecular artery to the trabecular vein.\" [MP:MP]\nsubset: pheno_slim\nsynonym: \"central arteriole\" BROAD []\nsynonym: \"follicular arteriole\" EXACT [MP:0002361]\nsynonym: \"splenic arteriole\" BROAD []\nsynonym: \"splenic central arteriole\" EXACT [MP:0002361]\nxref: MA:0000763\nis_a: UBERON:0001980 ! arteriole\nrelationship: connected_to UBERON:0010400 ! spleen trabecular vein\nrelationship: connecting_branch_of UBERON:0010399 {source=\"Wikipedia:Trabecular_arteries\"} ! spleen trabecular artery\nrelationship: contributes_to_morphology_of UBERON:0001959 ! white pulp of spleen\nrelationship: part_of UBERON:0001959 ! white pulp of spleen\n\n[Term]\nid: UBERON:0010408\nname: ocular angle artery\ndef: \"The angular artery is the terminal part of the facial artery; it ascends to the medial angle of the eye's orbit, imbedded in the fibers of the angular head of the Quadratus labii superioris, and accompanied by the angular vein.\" [MP:MP]\nsynonym: \"angular artery\" EXACT [FMA:49583]\nxref: EMAPA:37673 {source=\"MA:th\"}\nxref: FMA:49583\nxref: MA:0002010\nxref: NCIT:C32076\nxref: SCTID:145238006\nxref: UMLS:C0226116 {source=\"ncithesaurus:Angular_Artery\"}\nis_a: UBERON:0001637 ! artery\nrelationship: connecting_branch_of UBERON:0001612 ! facial artery\n\n[Term]\nid: UBERON:0011693\nname: extraembryonic portion of umbilical artery\nsynonym: \"extraembryonic umbilical artery\" EXACT [VHOG:0001157]\nxref: VHOG:0001157\nis_a: UBERON:0000478 {source=\"EHDAA2-abduced\"} ! extraembryonic structure\nis_a: UBERON:0001637 ! artery\nrelationship: connecting_branch_of UBERON:0001309 {source=\"FMA\"} ! internal iliac artery\nrelationship: part_of UBERON:0001310 ! umbilical artery\nrelationship: part_of UBERON:0007807 {source=\"EHDAA2-abduced\"} ! connecting stalk vasculature\n\n[Term]\nid: UBERON:0012321\nname: deep cervical artery\ndef: \"The deep cervical artery (Profunda cervicalis) is an artery of the neck.\" [Wikipedia:Deep_cervical_artery]\nsynonym: \"profunda cervicalis\" RELATED [Wikipedia:Deep_cervical_artery]\nxref: FMA:10659\nxref: SCTID:244223002\nxref: Wikipedia:Deep_cervical_artery\nintersection_of: UBERON:0012320 ! cervical artery\nintersection_of: part_of UBERON:0035551 ! deep vasculature\nrelationship: connecting_branch_of UBERON:0004688 {source=\"FMA\"} ! costo-cervical trunk\nrelationship: part_of UBERON:0000974 ! neck\n\n[Term]\nid: UBERON:0012322\nname: ascending cervical artery\ndef: \"The ascending cervical artery is a small branch which arises from the inferior thyroid artery as that vessel is passing behind the carotid sheath; it runs up on the anterior tubercles of the transverse processes of the cervical vertebrC& in the interval between the Scalenus anterior and Longus capitis. To the muscles of the neck it gives twigs which anastomose with branches of the vertebral, and it sends one or two spinal branches into the vertebral canal through the intervertebral foramina to be distributed to the medulla spinalis and its membranes, and to the bodies of the vertebrC&, in the same manner as the spinal branches from the vertebral. It anastomoses with the ascending pharyngeal and occipital arteries.\" [Wikipedia:Ascending_cervical_artery]\nsynonym: \"ascending cervical\" RELATED [Wikipedia:Ascending_cervical_artery]\nxref: FMA:52489\nxref: SCTID:161846001\nxref: Wikipedia:Ascending_cervical_artery\nis_a: UBERON:0012320 ! cervical artery\nrelationship: connecting_branch_of UBERON:0007149 {source=\"FMA\", source=\"Wikipedia\"} ! inferior thyroid artery\n\n[Term]\nid: UBERON:0013132\nname: penicillar arteriole\ndef: \"One of the small straight arteries of the red pulp of the spleen; a branch of the spleen central artery that supplies the red pulp[WP,modified].\" [http://www.merriam-webster.com/medical/penicillus, https://orcid.org/0000-0002-6601-2165]\nsynonym: \"penicillar artery\" RELATED []\nsynonym: \"penicilli\" EXACT OMO:0003004 [http://www.merriam-webster.com/medical/penicilli]\nsynonym: \"penicillus\" EXACT [FMA:16038]\nxref: FMA:16038\nis_a: UBERON:0001980 ! arteriole\nrelationship: connecting_branch_of UBERON:0010401 {source=\"Wikipedia:Trabecular_arteries\"} ! spleen central arteriole\nrelationship: part_of UBERON:0001959 {source=\"FMA\"} ! white pulp of spleen\nrelationship: vessel_supplies_blood_to UBERON:0001250 {source=\"Wikipedia:Trabecular_arteries\"} ! red pulp of spleen\n\n[Term]\nid: UBERON:0013648\nname: masseteric artery\ndef: \"The masseteric artery is small and passes laterally through the mandibular notch to the deep surface of the masseter muscle, which it supplies. It anastomoses with the masseteric branches of the external maxillary artery and with the transverse facial artery.\" [Wikipedia:Masseteric_artery]\nsynonym: \"arteria masseterica\" EXACT OMO:0003011 [Wikipedia:Masseteric_artery]\nxref: FMA:49739\nxref: NCIT:C53052\nxref: SCTID:147864007\nxref: UMLS:C0226149 {source=\"ncithesaurus:Masseteric_Artery\"}\nxref: Wikipedia:Masseteric_artery\nintersection_of: UBERON:0001637 ! artery\nintersection_of: vessel_supplies_blood_to UBERON:0001597 ! masseter muscle\nrelationship: connecting_branch_of UBERON:0001616 {source=\"FMA\"} ! maxillary artery\n\n[Term]\nid: UBERON:0014693\nname: inferior alveolar artery\nxref: FMA:49695\nxref: SCTID:276151008\nis_a: UBERON:0009654 ! alveolar artery\nrelationship: connecting_branch_of UBERON:0001616 {source=\"FMA\"} ! maxillary artery\n\n[Term]\nid: UBERON:0014694\nname: posterior auricular artery\ndef: \"The posterior auricular artery is a small artery and arises from the external carotid artery, above the Digastric muscle and Stylohyoid muscle, opposite the apex of the styloid process. It ascends posteriorly beneath the parotid gland, along the styloid process of the temporal bone, between the cartilage of the ear and the mastoid process of the temporal bone along the lateral side of the head. The posterior auricular artery supplies blood to the scalp posterior to the auricle and to the auricle itself.\" [Wikipedia:Posterior_auricular_artery]\nxref: FMA:49624\nxref: SCTID:244220004\nxref: Wikipedia:Posterior_auricular_artery\nis_a: UBERON:0009655 ! auricular artery\nrelationship: connecting_branch_of UBERON:0001070 {source=\"FMA\"} ! external carotid artery\nrelationship: vessel_supplies_blood_to UBERON:0001757 ! pinna\n\n[Term]\nid: UBERON:0014695\nname: deep auricular artery\ndef: \"The deep auricular artery often arises in common with the anterior tympanic artery. It ascends in the substance of the parotid gland, behind the temporomandibular articulation, pierces the cartilaginous or bony wall of the external acoustic meatus, and supplies its cuticular lining and the outer surface of the tympanic membrane. It gives a branch to the temporomandibular joint.\" [Wikipedia:Deep_auricular_artery]\nxref: FMA:49689\nxref: SCTID:147157007\nxref: Wikipedia:Deep_auricular_artery\nintersection_of: UBERON:0009655 ! auricular artery\nintersection_of: part_of UBERON:0035551 ! deep vasculature\nrelationship: connecting_branch_of UBERON:0001616 {source=\"FMA\"} ! maxillary artery\nrelationship: vessel_supplies_blood_to UBERON:0010069 ! outer epithelial layer of tympanic membrane\n\n[Term]\nid: UBERON:0014696\nname: anterior choroidal artery\ndef: \"The anterior choroidal artery originates from the internal carotid artery, though it also rarely arises from the middle cerebral artery.\" [Wikipedia:Anterior_choroidal_artery]\nsynonym: \"anterior choroidal\" RELATED [Wikipedia:Anterior_choroidal_artery]\nxref: FMA:50087\nxref: NCIT:C32083\nxref: SCTID:244211008\nxref: Wikipedia:Anterior_choroidal_artery\nis_a: UBERON:0013151 ! choroidal artery\ndisjoint_from: UBERON:0014697 {source=\"lexical\"} ! posterior choroidal artery\nrelationship: connecting_branch_of UBERON:0001532 {source=\"FMA\"} ! internal carotid artery\n\n[Term]\nid: UBERON:0014697\nname: posterior choroidal artery\nxref: FMA:50657\nxref: NCIT:C33352\nxref: SCTID:369342007\nis_a: UBERON:0013151 ! choroidal artery\nrelationship: connecting_branch_of UBERON:0001636 {source=\"FMA\"} ! posterior cerebral artery\nrelationship: part_of UBERON:0001636 {source=\"FMA\"} ! posterior cerebral artery\n\n[Term]\nid: UBERON:0014772\nname: lateral palpebral artery\ndef: \"The lateral palpebral arteries are small arteries which supply the eyelid.\" [Wikipedia:Lateral_palpebral_arteries]\nsynonym: \"lateral palpebral branch of ophthalmic artery\" EXACT [FMA:49940]\nsynonym: \"lateral palpebral branches\" RELATED [Wikipedia:Lateral_palpebral_arteries]\nxref: FMA:49940\nxref: SCTID:369323008\nxref: Wikipedia:Lateral_palpebral_arteries\nis_a: UBERON:0014770 ! palpebral artery\ndisjoint_from: UBERON:0014773 {source=\"lexical\"} ! medial palpebral artery\nrelationship: connecting_branch_of UBERON:0001622 {source=\"FMA\"} ! lacrimal artery\n\n[Term]\nid: UBERON:0014773\nname: medial palpebral artery\ndef: \"The medial palpebral arteries (internal palpebral arteries) are arteries of the head. They are two in number, superior and inferior, arise from the ophthalmic, opposite the pulley of the Obliquus superior.\" [Wikipedia:Medial_palpebral_arteries]\nsynonym: \"inferior palpebral artery\" RELATED [Wikipedia:Medial_palpebral_arteries]\nsynonym: \"internal palpebral arteries\" RELATED [Wikipedia:Medial_palpebral_arteries]\nsynonym: \"internal palpebral artery\" RELATED [Wikipedia:Medial_palpebral_arteries]\nsynonym: \"medial palpebral branch of ophthalmic artery\" EXACT [FMA:50012]\nsynonym: \"superior palpebral\" RELATED [Wikipedia:Medial_palpebral_arteries]\nsynonym: \"superior palpebral artery\" RELATED [Wikipedia:Medial_palpebral_arteries]\nxref: FMA:50012\nxref: SCTID:369331003\nxref: Wikipedia:Medial_palpebral_arteries\nis_a: UBERON:0014770 ! palpebral artery\nrelationship: connecting_branch_of UBERON:0001619 {source=\"FMA\"} ! ophthalmic artery\n\n[Term]\nid: UBERON:0015156\nname: terminal branch of ophthalmic artery\ndef: \"The two terminal branches of the ophthalmic artery in humans are the dorsal nasal artery and the supratrochlear artery.\" [Wikipedia:Dorsal_nasal_artery, Wikipedia:Supratrochlear_artery]\nxref: FMA:51956\nis_a: UBERON:0001637 ! artery\nrelationship: connecting_branch_of UBERON:0001619 ! ophthalmic artery\n\n[Term]\nid: UBERON:0015157\nname: zygomatico-orbital artery\ndef: \"The middle temporal artery occasionally gives off a zygomatico-orbital branch, which runs along the upper border of the zygomatic arch, between the two layers of the temporal fascia, to the lateral angle of the orbit. This branch, which may arise directly from the superficial temporal artery, supplies the Orbicularis oculi, and anastomoses with the lacrimal and palpebral branches of the ophthalmic artery.\" [Wikipedia:Zygomatico-orbital_artery]\nsynonym: \"zygomaticooerbital branch\" RELATED [Wikipedia:Zygomatico-orbital_artery]\nsynonym: \"zygomaticoorbital branch\" RELATED [Wikipedia:Zygomatico-orbital_artery]\nxref: FMA:49663\nxref: SCTID:146753008\nxref: Wikipedia:Zygomatico-orbital_artery\nis_a: UBERON:0001637 ! artery\nrelationship: connecting_branch_of UBERON:0001614 {source=\"FMA\"} ! superficial temporal artery\n\n[Term]\nid: UBERON:0015158\nname: ophthalmotemporal branch of external ophthalmic artery\ncomment: The blood supply to the (Harderian) gland has been reported in greatest detail in the sparrow Passer domesticus (Slonaker, 1918), where it is derived through the ophthalmotemporal branch of the external ophthalmic artery http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/7559104\nsynonym: \"ophthalmotemporal artery\" RELATED []\nis_a: UBERON:0001637 ! artery\nrelationship: connecting_branch_of UBERON:0001619 ! ophthalmic artery\nrelationship: vessel_supplies_blood_to UBERON:0004187 {source=\"PMID:7559104\"} ! Harderian gland\n\n[Term]\nid: UBERON:0015160\nname: supraorbital artery\ndef: \"The supraorbital artery is an artery of the head. It springs from the ophthalmic artery as that vessel is crossing over to the medial side of the optic nerve.\" [Wikipedia:Supraorbital_artery]\nsynonym: \"arteria supraorbitalis\" EXACT OMO:0003011 [Wikipedia:Supraorbital_artery]\nsynonym: \"supra-orbital artery\" EXACT [FMA:49973]\nsynonym: \"supraorbital artery\" EXACT [FMA:49973]\nsynonym: \"supraorbital branch of external ophthalmic artery\" RELATED []\nxref: FMA:49973\nxref: SCTID:369330002\nxref: Wikipedia:Supraorbital_artery\nis_a: UBERON:0001637 ! artery\nrelationship: connecting_branch_of UBERON:0001619 ! ophthalmic artery\nrelationship: vessel_supplies_blood_to UBERON:0001604 ! levator palpebrae superioris\nrelationship: vessel_supplies_blood_to UBERON:0005027 ! mucosa of frontal sinus\n\n[Term]\nid: UBERON:0015480\nname: proper hepatic artery\ndef: \"The hepatic artery proper (also proper hepatic artery), arises from the common hepatic artery and runs alongside the portal vein and the common bile duct to form the portal triad. The hepatic artery proper gives off a small supraduodenal artery to the duodenal bulb. Then the right gastric artery comes off and runs to the left along the lesser curvature of the stomach to meet the left gastric artery, which is a branch of the celiac trunk. It subsequently gives off the cystic artery, which feeds the gallbladder, before bifurcating into the right and left hepatic arteries. Of note, the right and left hepatic arteries may demonstrate variant anatomy. A replaced right hepatic artery may arise from the superior mesenteric artery (SMA) and a replaced left hepatic artery may arise from the left gastric artery.\" [Wikipedia:Hepatic_artery_proper]\nsynonym: \"hepatic artery proper\" EXACT [FMA:14772]\nsynonym: \"proper hepatic\" RELATED [Wikipedia:Hepatic_artery_proper]\nxref: EMAPA:37217 {source=\"MA:th\"}\nxref: FMA:14772\nxref: MA:0003095\nxref: SCTID:244262006\nxref: Wikipedia:Hepatic_artery_proper\nis_a: UBERON:0001193 {source=\"MA\"} ! hepatic artery\nrelationship: connecting_branch_of UBERON:0005436 {source=\"FMA\"} ! common hepatic artery\n\n[Term]\nid: UBERON:0018231\nname: labyrinthine artery\ndef: \"A long slender branch of the anterior inferior cerebellar artery (85%-100% cases) or basilar artery (<15% cases), arises from near the middle of the artery; it accompanies the vestibulocochlear nerve through the internal acoustic meatus, and is distributed to the internal ear.\" [Wikipedia:Labyrinthine_artery]\nsynonym: \"arteria auditiva interna\" EXACT OMO:0003011 [Wikipedia:Labyrinthine_artery]\nsynonym: \"arteria labyrinthi\" EXACT OMO:0003011 [Wikipedia:Labyrinthine_artery]\nsynonym: \"artery of inner ear\" BROAD [FMA:50548]\nsynonym: \"internal auditory artery\" EXACT [FMA:50548]\nxref: EMAPA:37093 {source=\"MA:th\"}\nxref: FMA:50548\nxref: NCIT:C32834\nxref: SCTID:148672009\nxref: Wikipedia:Labyrinthine_artery\nis_a: UBERON:0001637 ! artery\nrelationship: branching_part_of UBERON:0009689 {gci_relation=\"part_of\", gci_filler=\"NCBITaxon:9606\", cases=\"85-100%\", source=\"WP\"} ! anterior inferior cerebellar artery\nrelationship: connecting_branch_of UBERON:0001633 {gci_relation=\"part_of\", gci_filler=\"NCBITaxon:9606\", cases=\"15%\", source=\"WP\"} ! basilar artery\nrelationship: part_of UBERON:0001846 ! internal ear\n\n[Term]\nid: UBERON:0018243\nname: thymic artery\ndef: \"A vein that supplies blood to the thymus.\" [http://orcid.org/0000-0002-6601-2165]\ncomment: The arteries supplying the thymus are derived from the internal thoracic artery, and from the superior thyroid artery and inferior thyroids.[WP]\nsynonym: \"thymic arteries\" RELATED OMO:0003004 [Wikipedia:Thymic_branches_of_internal_thoracic_artery]\nsynonym: \"thymic branch of internal thoracic artery\" EXACT [FMA:10647]\nxref: FMA:10647\nxref: SCTID:76543001\nxref: Wikipedia:Thymic_branches_of_internal_thoracic_artery\nintersection_of: UBERON:0001637 ! artery\nintersection_of: vessel_supplies_blood_to UBERON:0002370 ! thymus\nrelationship: connecting_branch_of UBERON:0002456 {source=\"FMA\"} ! internal thoracic artery\n\n[Term]\nid: UBERON:0018250\nname: middle thyroid artery\nis_a: UBERON:0003847 ! thyroid artery\nrelationship: connecting_branch_of UBERON:0001070 {source=\"PMC1167197\"} ! external carotid artery\nproperty_value: taxon_notes \"In Cavio cobaya, arises from the external carotid or distal half of the common carotid artery, passed the thyroid gland cranially or penetrated it to terminate in the inferior laryngeal artery\" xsd:string\n\n[Term]\nid: UBERON:0018397\nname: posterior superior alveolar artery\ndef: \"The posterior superior alveolar artery (posterior dental artery) is given off from the maxillary, frequently in conjunction with the infraorbital just as the trunk of the vessel is passing into the pterygopalatine fossa.\" [Wikipedia:Posterior_superior_alveolar_artery]\nsynonym: \"superior posterior alveolar artery\" EXACT [FMA:49757]\nxref: FMA:49757\nxref: Wikipedia:Posterior_superior_alveolar_artery\nis_a: UBERON:0001637 ! artery\nrelationship: connecting_branch_of UBERON:0001616 {source=\"FMA\"} ! maxillary artery\n\n[Term]\nid: UBERON:0034693\nname: cremasteric artery\ndef: \"The cremasteric artery (external spermatic artery) is a branch of the Inferior epigastric artery which accompanies the spermatic cord, and supplies the Cremaster and other coverings of the cord, anastomosing with the testicular artery (internal spermatic artery in older texts). (In the female, the cremesteric artery is very small and accompanies the round ligament.).\" [Wikipedia:Cremasteric_artery]\nsynonym: \"cremasteric part of inferior epigastric artery\" EXACT [FMA:70192]\nsynonym: \"external spermatic artery\" RELATED [Wikipedia:Cremasteric_artery]\nxref: FMA:70192\nxref: SCTID:279658002\nxref: Wikipedia:Cremasteric_artery\nis_a: UBERON:0001637 ! artery\nrelationship: connecting_branch_of UBERON:0001354 {source=\"FMA\"} ! inferior epigastric artery\nrelationship: part_of UBERON:0001354 {source=\"FMA\"} ! inferior epigastric artery\n\n[Term]\nid: UBERON:0034727\nname: vestibular bulb artery\ndef: \"The artery of bulb of vestibule is a branch of the internal pudendal artery.\" [Wikipedia:Artery_of_bulb_of_vestibule]\nsynonym: \"arteria bulbi vestibuli\" EXACT OMO:0003011 [FMA:TA]\nsynonym: \"artery of bulb of vestibule\" EXACT [FMA:20900]\nxref: FMA:20900\nxref: SCTID:293541004\nxref: Wikipedia:Artery_of_bulb_of_vestibule\nintersection_of: UBERON:0001637 ! artery\nintersection_of: vessel_supplies_blood_to UBERON:0013129 ! bulb of vestibule\nrelationship: connecting_branch_of UBERON:0007315 {source=\"FMA\"} ! internal pudendal artery\n\n[Term]\nid: UBERON:0034927\nname: arcuate artery of foot\ndef: \"The arcuate artery of the foot (metatarsal artery) arises a little anterior to the lateral tarsal artery; it passes lateralward, over the bases of the metatarsal bones, beneath the tendons of the Extensor digitorum brevis, its direction being influenced by its point of origin; and its anastomoses with the lateral tarsal and lateral plantar arteries. This vessel gives off the second, third, and fourth dorsal metatarsal arteries. It is not present in all individuals.\" [Wikipedia:Arcuate_artery_of_the_foot]\nxref: FMA:44594\nxref: SCTID:244331005\nxref: Wikipedia:Arcuate_artery_of_the_foot\nis_a: UBERON:0001637 ! artery\nrelationship: connecting_branch_of UBERON:0001537 {source=\"FMA\"} ! anterior tibial artery\nrelationship: part_of UBERON:0002387 ! pes\n\n[Term]\nid: UBERON:0035040\nname: superior rectal artery\ndef: \"The superior rectal artery (superior hemorrhoidal artery) is an artery that descends into the pelvis to supply blood to the rectum.\" [Wikipedia:Superior_rectal_artery]\nsynonym: \"superior hemorrhoidal\" RELATED [Wikipedia:Superior_rectal_artery]\nsynonym: \"superior hemorrhoidal artery\" EXACT [FMA:14832]\nsynonym: \"superior hemorrhoidal artery\" RELATED [Wikipedia:Superior_rectal_artery]\nsynonym: \"superior rectal\" RELATED [Wikipedia:Superior_rectal_artery]\nxref: FMA:14832\nxref: NCIT:C33677\nxref: SCTID:244278008\nxref: Wikipedia:Superior_rectal_artery\nis_a: UBERON:0035039 ! rectal artery\nrelationship: connecting_branch_of UBERON:0001183 {source=\"FMA\"} ! inferior mesenteric artery\nrelationship: part_of UBERON:0001183 {source=\"FMA\"} ! inferior mesenteric artery\n\n[Term]\nid: UBERON:0035041\nname: deep temporal artery\ndef: \"The deep temporal arteries, two in number, anterior and posterior, ascend between the Temporalis and the pericranium. They supply the muscle, and anastomose with the middle temporal artery. The anterior communicates with the lacrimal artery by means of small branches which perforate the zygomatic bone and great wing of the sphenoid.\" [Wikipedia:Deep_temporal_arteries]\nsynonym: \"anterior deep temporal artery\" RELATED [Wikipedia:Deep_temporal_arteries]\nsynonym: \"deep temporal arteries\" RELATED [Wikipedia:Deep_temporal_arteries]\nsynonym: \"deep temporal artery\" RELATED [Wikipedia:Deep_temporal_arteries]\nsynonym: \"deep temporal branches\" RELATED [Wikipedia:Deep_temporal_arteries]\nsynonym: \"posterior deep temporal artery\" RELATED [Wikipedia:Deep_temporal_arteries]\nxref: FMA:49742\nxref: SCTID:147965009\nxref: Wikipedia:Deep_temporal_arteries\nintersection_of: UBERON:0001632 ! temporal artery\nintersection_of: part_of UBERON:0035551 ! deep vasculature\nrelationship: connecting_branch_of UBERON:0001616 {source=\"FMA\"} ! maxillary artery\n\n[Term]\nid: UBERON:0035042\nname: middle temporal artery\ndef: \"The middle temporal artery arises immediately above the zygomatic arch, and, perforating the temporal fascia, gives branches to the Temporalis, anastomosing with the deep temporal branches of the internal maxillary. It occasionally gives off a zygomaticoC6rbital branch, which runs along the upper border of the zygomatic arch, between the two layers of the temporal fascia, to the lateral angle of the orbit.\" [Wikipedia:Middle_temporal_artery]\nsynonym: \"middle temporal artery\" RELATED [Wikipedia:Middle_temporal_artery]\nxref: FMA:49666\nxref: SCTID:146854006\nxref: Wikipedia:Middle_temporal_artery\nis_a: UBERON:0001632 ! temporal artery\nrelationship: connecting_branch_of UBERON:0001614 {source=\"FMA\"} ! superficial temporal artery\n\n[Term]\nid: UBERON:0035180\nname: sigmoid artery\ndef: \"The sigmoid arteries, two or three in number, run obliquely downward and to the left behind the peritoneum and in front of the Psoas major, ureter, and internal spermatic vessels. Their branches supply the lower part of the descending colon, the iliac colon, and the sigmoid or pelvic colon; anastomosing above with the left colic, and below with the superior hemorrhoidal artery.\" [Wikipedia:Sigmoid_arteries]\nsynonym: \"inferior left colic artery\" EXACT [FMA:14830]\nxref: FMA:14830\nxref: NCIT:C33549\nxref: SCTID:265956005\nxref: UMLS:C0226330\nxref: Wikipedia:Sigmoid_arteries\nis_a: UBERON:0001637 ! artery\nrelationship: connecting_branch_of UBERON:0001183 {source=\"FMA\"} ! inferior mesenteric artery\n\n[Term]\nid: UBERON:0035222\nname: posterior parietal artery\nxref: FMA:50488\nxref: NCIT:C33372\nxref: SCTID:44894007\nxref: UMLS:C0226227\nis_a: UBERON:0001637 ! artery\ndisjoint_from: UBERON:0035462 {source=\"lexical\"} ! anterior parietal artery\nrelationship: connecting_branch_of UBERON:0001627 {source=\"FMA\"} ! middle cerebral artery\n\n[Term]\nid: UBERON:0035225\nname: anterior temporal artery\ndef: \"A branch of the middle cerebral artery that supplies blood to the anterior part of the temporal lobe.\" [ncithesaurus:Anterior_Temporal_Artery]\nxref: FMA:50382\nxref: NCIT:C32113\nxref: SCTID:44310009\nxref: UMLS:C0226228\nis_a: UBERON:0001632 {source=\"FMA\"} ! temporal artery\ndisjoint_from: UBERON:0035261 {source=\"lexical\"} ! posterior temporal artery\nrelationship: connecting_branch_of UBERON:0001627 {source=\"FMA\"} ! middle cerebral artery\n\n[Term]\nid: UBERON:0035261\nname: posterior temporal artery\nxref: FMA:50458\nxref: NCIT:C33384\nxref: SCTID:23830002\nxref: UMLS:C0226229\nis_a: UBERON:0001632 {source=\"FMA\"} ! temporal artery\nrelationship: connecting_branch_of UBERON:0001627 {source=\"FMA\"} ! middle cerebral artery\n\n[Term]\nid: UBERON:0035273\nname: superior thoracic artery\ndef: \"The superior thoracic artery (highest thoracic artery) is a small vessel normally arising from the first division of the axillary artery, but may arise from the thoracoacromial artery, itself a branch of the second division of the axillary artery. Running forward and medialward along the upper border of the pectoralis minor, the superior thoracic artery passes between it and the pectoralis major to the side of the chest. It supplies branches to the first and second intercostal spaces as well as to the superior portion of serratus anterior. It anastomoses with the internal mammary and intercostal arteries.\" [Wikipedia:Superior_thoracic_artery]\nxref: FMA:22668\nxref: NCIT:C33701\nxref: SCTID:198713000\nxref: UMLS:C0226419\nxref: Wikipedia:Superior_thoracic_artery\nis_a: UBERON:0001637 ! artery\nrelationship: connecting_branch_of UBERON:0001394 {source=\"FMA\"} ! axillary artery\n\n[Term]\nid: UBERON:0035404\nname: superior hypophysial artery\ndef: \"The superior hypophysial artery is an artery supplying the pars tuberalis,the infundibulum of the pituitary gland and the median eminence. It is a branch of the posterior communicating artery which branches from the internal carotid artery in the circle of Willis..\" [Wikipedia:Superior_hypophysial_artery]\nsynonym: \"superior hypophyseal artery\" EXACT [FMA:49849]\nxref: FMA:49849\nxref: NCIT:C33678\nxref: SCTID:303427008\nxref: UMLS:C1261387\nxref: Wikipedia:Superior_hypophysial_artery\nis_a: UBERON:0001637 ! artery\nrelationship: connecting_branch_of UBERON:0001532 ! internal carotid artery\nrelationship: vessel_supplies_blood_to UBERON:0000007 ! pituitary gland\n\n[Term]\nid: UBERON:0035422\nname: circumflex branch of left coronary artery\ndef: \"Branch of left coronary artery which runs perpendicular to the anterior interventricular branch of the left coronary artery on the left side of the interventricular sulcus and supplies the left side of the heart.\" [FMA:3895]\nsynonym: \"circumflex coronary artery\" EXACT [FMA:3895]\nsynonym: \"left circumflex branch of left coronary artery\" EXACT [FMA:3895]\nsynonym: \"ramus circumflexus (arteria coronaria sinistra)\" EXACT OMO:0003011 [FMA:3895, FMA:TA]\nxref: FMA:3895\nxref: NCIT:C12874\nxref: SCTID:362036002\nxref: UMLS:C0226037\nxref: Wikipedia:Circumflex_branch_of_left_coronary_artery\nis_a: UBERON:0001637 ! artery\nrelationship: connecting_branch_of UBERON:0001626 {source=\"FMA\"} ! left coronary artery\nrelationship: part_of UBERON:0001626 {source=\"FMA\"} ! left coronary artery\n\n[Term]\nid: UBERON:0035462\nname: anterior parietal artery\ndef: \"The artery that delivers blood to the anterior portion of the parietal lobe.\" [ncithesaurus:Anterior_Parietal_Artery]\nxref: FMA:50485\nxref: NCIT:C32101\nxref: SCTID:78499006\nxref: UMLS:C0226226\nis_a: UBERON:0001637 ! artery\nrelationship: connecting_branch_of UBERON:0001627 {source=\"FMA\"} ! middle cerebral artery\n\n[Term]\nid: UBERON:0035492\nname: inferior hypophysial artery\ndef: \"The inferior hypophysial artery is an artery supplying the pituitary gland. It is a branch of the cavernous carotid artery (internal carotid artery).\" [Wikipedia:Inferior_hypophysial_artery]\nsynonym: \"inferior hypophyseal artery\" EXACT [FMA:49846]\nxref: FMA:49846\nxref: NCIT:C32777\nxref: SCTID:303428003\nxref: UMLS:C1261083\nxref: Wikipedia:Inferior_hypophysial_artery\nis_a: UBERON:0001637 ! artery\nrelationship: connecting_branch_of UBERON:0001532 ! internal carotid artery\nrelationship: vessel_supplies_blood_to UBERON:0000007 ! pituitary gland\n\n[Term]\nid: UBERON:0035829\nname: right gastroepiploic artery\ndef: \"Artery that runs from right to left along the greater curvature of the stomach, between the layers of the greater omentum, anastomosing with the left gastroepiploic branch of the splenic artery.\" [Wikipedia:Right_gastro-omental_artery]\nsynonym: \"arteria gastro-omentalis dextra\" EXACT OMO:0003011 [Wikipedia:Right_gastro-omental_artery]\nsynonym: \"arteria gastroepiploica dextra\" EXACT OMO:0003011 [Wikipedia:Right_gastro-omental_artery]\nsynonym: \"arteria gastroomentalis dextra\" EXACT OMO:0003011 [Wikipedia:Right_gastro-omental_artery]\nsynonym: \"right gastro-epiploic artery\" EXACT [FMA:14781]\nsynonym: \"right gastro-omental artery\" EXACT [FMA:14781]\nsynonym: \"right gastroepiploic\" RELATED [Wikipedia:Right_gastro-omental_artery]\nsynonym: \"right gastroepiploic artery\" RELATED [Wikipedia:Right_gastro-omental_artery]\nsynonym: \"right gastroomental artery\" EXACT [FMA:14781]\nxref: FMA:14781\nxref: SCTID:244271002\nxref: Wikipedia:Right_gastro-omental_artery\nis_a: UBERON:0009025 ! gastroepiploic artery\nrelationship: connecting_branch_of UBERON:0010132 {source=\"FMA\"} ! gastroduodenal artery\nrelationship: vessel_supplies_blood_to UBERON:0002108 {source=\"FMA\"} ! small intestine\n\n[Term]\nid: UBERON:0035830\nname: left gastroepiploic artery\ndef: \"Artery that runs from left to right along the greater curvature of the stomach, between the layers of the greater omentum, and anastomoses with the right gastroepiploic.\" [Wikipedia:Left_gastro-omental_artery]\nsynonym: \"arteria gastro-omentalis sinistra\" EXACT OMO:0003011 [Wikipedia:Left_gastro-omental_artery]\nsynonym: \"arteria gastroepiploica sinistra\" EXACT OMO:0003011 [Wikipedia:Left_gastro-omental_artery]\nsynonym: \"arteria gastroomentalis sinistra\" EXACT OMO:0003011 [Wikipedia:Left_gastro-omental_artery]\nsynonym: \"left gastro-epiploic artery\" EXACT [FMA:14796]\nsynonym: \"left gastro-omental artery\" EXACT [FMA:14796]\nsynonym: \"left gastroepiploic artery\" RELATED [Wikipedia:Left_gastro-omental_artery]\nsynonym: \"left gastroepiploic branch\" RELATED [Wikipedia:Left_gastro-omental_artery]\nsynonym: \"left gastroomental artery\" EXACT [FMA:14796]\nsynonym: \"left inferior gastric artery\" EXACT [FMA:14796]\nxref: FMA:14796\nxref: SCTID:244270001\nxref: Wikipedia:Left_gastro-omental_artery\nis_a: UBERON:0009025 ! gastroepiploic artery\nrelationship: connecting_branch_of UBERON:0001194 {source=\"FMA\"} ! splenic artery\n\n[Term]\nid: UBERON:0039215\nname: appendicular artery\ndef: \"An artery that commonly arises from the terminal branch of the ileocolic artery, or less commonly from the posterior cecal artery or an ileal artery.[1][2] It descends behind the termination of the ileum and enters the mesoappendix of the vermiform appendix. It runs near the free margin of the mesoappendix and ends in branches which supply the appendix.\" [https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Appendicular_artery]\nsynonym: \"appendiceal artery\" EXACT [FMA:14818]\nxref: FMA:14818\nis_a: UBERON:0001637 ! artery\nrelationship: connecting_branch_of UBERON:0001197 ! ileocolic artery\nrelationship: vessel_supplies_blood_to UBERON:0001154 {source=\"FMA\"} ! vermiform appendix\n\n[Term]\nid: UBERON:0039261\nname: pancreatic artery\nxref: FMA:70471\nintersection_of: UBERON:0001637 ! artery\nintersection_of: vessel_supplies_blood_to UBERON:0001264 ! pancreas\nrelationship: connecting_branch_of UBERON:0001194 ! splenic artery\n\n[Term]\nid: UBERON:0039351\nname: posterior labial artery\nsynonym: \"posterior labial branch of internal pudendal artery\" EXACT [FMA:20886]\nxref: FMA:20886\nis_a: UBERON:0001637 ! artery\nrelationship: connecting_branch_of UBERON:0001358 {source=\"FMA\"} ! perineal artery\n\n[Term]\nid: UBERON:8410022\nname: left colic artery\ndef: \"The first branch of the inferior mesenteric artery (IMA) is the left colic artery. The left colic artery supplies blood flow to the distal third of the transverse colon and the entirety of the descending colon. Once diverging from the IMA, the left colic artery runs anterior to the left ureter, left internal spermatic vessels (males), and psoas major before branching into its ascending and descending segments.\" [https://orcid.org/0000-0003-4183-8865, PMID:29489246]\nxref: FMA:14826\nis_a: UBERON:0001637 ! artery\nrelationship: connecting_branch_of UBERON:0001183 ! inferior mesenteric artery\nrelationship: dc-contributor https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2825-0621 ! Paola Roncaglia\nrelationship: vessel_supplies_blood_to UBERON:0001157 ! transverse colon\nrelationship: vessel_supplies_blood_to UBERON:0001158 ! descending colon\n\n[Term]\nid: UBERON:8410035\nname: medullary arteriole of lymph node\ndef: \"An arteriole that arises from the hilar artery of a lymph node and radiates centrifugally, branching in the medulla.\" [http://orcid.org/0000-0003-3440-1876, PMID:17067937]\nsynonym: \"arteriole of medulla of lymph node\" EXACT []\nintersection_of: UBERON:0001980 ! arteriole\nintersection_of: part_of UBERON:0002007 ! medulla of lymph node\nrelationship: connecting_branch_of UBERON:8410034 ! lymph node artery\nrelationship: dc-contributor https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2825-0621 ! Paola Roncaglia\n\n","metadata":{"output":"...\n\n223002\nxref: Wikipedia:Deep_cervical_artery\nintersection_of: UBERON:0012320 ! cervical artery\nintersection_of: part_of UBERON:0035551 ! deep vasculature\nrelationship: connecting_branch_of UBERON:0004688 {source=\"FMA\"} ! costo-cervical trunk\nrelationship: part_of UBERON:0000974 ! neck\n\n[Term]\nid: UBERON:0012322\nname: ascending cervical artery\ndef: \"The ascending cervical artery is a small branch which arises from the inferior thyroid artery as that vessel is passing behind the carotid sheath; it runs up on the anterior tubercles of the transverse processes of the cervical vertebrC& in the interval between the Scalenus anterior and Longus capitis. To the muscles of the neck it gives twigs which anastomose with branches of the vertebral, and it sends one or two spinal branches into the vertebral canal through the intervertebral foramina to be distributed to the medulla spinalis and its membranes, and to the bodies of the vertebrC&, in the same manner as the spinal branches from the vertebral. It anastomoses with the ascending pharyngeal and occipital arteries.\" [Wikipedia:Ascending_cervical_artery]\nsynonym: \"ascending cervical\" RELATED [Wikipedia:Ascending_cervical_artery]\nxref: FMA:52489\nxref: SCTID:161846001\nxref: Wikipedia:Ascending_cervical_artery\nis_a: UBERON:0012320 ! cervical artery\nrelationship: connecting_branch_of UBERON:0007149 {source=\"FMA\", source=\"Wikipedia\"} ! inferior thyroid artery\n\n[Term]\nid: UBERON:0013132\nname: penicillar arteriole\ndef: \"One of the small straight arteries of the red pulp of the spleen; a branch of the spleen central artery that supplies the red pulp[WP,modified].\" [http://www.merriam-webster.com/medical/penicillus, https://orcid.org/0000-0002-6601-2165]\nsynonym: \"penicillar artery\" RELATED []\nsynonym: \"penicilli\" EXACT OMO:0003004 [http://www.merriam-webster.com/medical/penicilli]\nsynonym: \"penicillus\" EXACT [FMA:16038]\nxref: FMA:16038\nis_a: UBERON:0001980 ! arteriole\nrelationship: connecting_branch_of UBERON:0010401 {source=\"Wikipedia:Trabecular_arteries\"} ! spleen central arteriole\nrelationship: part_of UBERON:0001959 {source=\"FMA\"} ! white pulp of spleen\nrelationship: vessel_supplies_blood_to UBERON:0001250 {source=\"Wikipedia:Trabecular_arteries\"} ! red pulp of spleen\n\n[Term]\nid: UBERON:0013648\nname: masseteric artery\ndef: \"The masseteric artery is small and passes laterally through the mandibular notch to the deep surface of the masseter muscle, which it supplies. It anastomoses with the masseteric branches of the external maxillary artery and with the transverse facial artery.\" [Wikipedia:Masseteric_artery]\nsynonym: \"arteria masseterica\" EXACT OMO:0003011 [Wikipedia:Masseteric_artery]\nxref: FMA:49739\nxref: NCIT:C53052\nxref: SCTID:147864007\nxref: UMLS:C0226149 {source=\"ncithesaurus:Masseteric_Artery\"}\nxref: Wikipedia:Masseteric_artery\nintersection_of: UBERON:0001637 ! artery\nintersection_of: vessel_supplies_blood_to UBERON:0001597 ! masseter muscle\nrelationship: connecting_branch_of UBERON:0001616 {source=\"FMA\"} ! maxillary artery\n\n[Term]\nid: UBERON:0014693\nname: inferior alveolar artery\nxref: FMA:49695\nxref: SCTID:276151008\nis_a: UBERON:0009654 ! alveolar artery\nrelationship: connecting_branch_of UBERON:0001616 {source=\"FMA\"} ! maxillary artery\n\n[Term]\nid: UBERON:0014694\nname: posterior auricular artery\ndef: \"The posterior auricular artery is a small artery and arises from the external carotid artery, above the Digastric muscle and Stylohyoid muscle, opposite the apex of the styloid process. It ascends posteriorly beneath the parotid gland, along the styloid process of the temporal bone, between the cartilage of the ear and the mastoid process of the temporal bone along the lateral side of the head. The posterior auricular artery supplies blood to the scalp posterior to the auricle and to the auricle itself.\" [Wikipedia:Posterior_auricular_artery]\nxref: FMA:49624\nxref: SCTID:244220004\nxref: Wikipedia:Posterior_auricular_artery\nis_a: UBERON:0009655 ! auricular artery\nrelationship: connecting_branch_of UBERON:0001070 {source=\"FMA\"} ! external carotid artery\nrelationship: vessel_supplies_blood_to UBERON:0001757 ! pinna\n\n[Term]\nid: UBERON:0014695\nname: deep auricular artery\ndef: \"The deep auricular artery often arises in common with the anterior tympanic artery. It ascends in the substance of the parotid gland, behind the temporomandibular articulation, pierces the cartilaginous or bony wall of the external acoustic meatus, and supplies its cuticular lining and the outer surface of the tympanic membrane. It gives a branch to the temporomandibular joint.\" [Wikipedia:Deep_auricular_artery]\nxref: FMA:49689\nxref: SCTID:147157007\nxref: Wikipedia:Deep_auricular_artery\nintersection_of: UBERON:0009655 ! auricular artery\nintersection_of: part_of UBERON:0035551 ! deep vasculature\nrelationship: connecting_branch_of UBERON:0001616 {source=\"FMA\"} ! maxillary artery\nrelationship: vessel_supplies_blood_to UBERON:0010069 ! outer epithelial layer of tympanic membrane\n\n[Term]\nid: UBERON:0014696\nname: anterior choroidal artery\ndef: \"The anterior choroidal artery originates from the internal carotid artery, though it also rarely arises from the middle cerebral artery.\" [Wikipedia:Anterior_choroidal_artery]\nsynonym: \"anterior choroidal\" RELATED [Wikipedia:Anterior_choroidal_artery]\nxref: FMA:50087\nxref: NCIT:C32083\nxref: SCTID:244211008\nxref: Wikipedia:Anterior_choroidal_artery\nis_a: UBERON:0013151 ! choroidal artery\ndisjoint_from: UBERON:0014697 {source=\"lexical\"} ! posterior choroidal artery\nrelationship: connecting_branch_of UBERON:0001532 {source=\"FMA\"} ! internal carotid artery\n\n[Term]\nid: UBERON:0014697\nname: posterior choroidal artery\nxref: FMA:50657\nxref: NCIT:C33352\nxref: SCTID:369342007\nis_a: UBERON:0013151 ! choroidal artery\nrelationship: connecting_branch_of UBERON:0001636 {source=\"FMA\"} ! posterior cerebral artery\nrelationship: part_of UBERON:0001636 {source=\"FMA\"} ! posterior cerebral artery\n\n[Term]\nid: UBERON:0014772\nname: lateral palpebral artery\ndef: \"The lateral palpebral arteries are small arteries which supply the eyelid.\" [Wikipedia:Lateral_palpebral_arteries]\nsynonym: \"lateral palpebral branch of ophthalmic artery\" EXACT [FMA:49940]\nsynonym: \"lateral palpebral branches\" RELATED [Wikipedia:Lateral_palpebral_arteries]\nxref: FMA:49940\nxref: SCTID:369323008\nxref: Wikipedia:Lateral_palpebral_arteries\nis_a: UBERON:0014770 ! palpebral artery\ndisjoint_from: UBERON:0014773 {source=\"lexical\"} ! medial palpebral artery\nrelationship: connecting_branch_of UBERON:0001622 {source=\"FMA\"} ! lacrimal artery\n\n[Term]\nid: UBERON:0014773\nname: medial palpebral artery\ndef: \"The medial palpebral arteries (internal palpebral arteries) are arteries of the head. They are two in number, superior and inferior, arise from the ophthalmic, opposite the pulley of the Obliquus superior.\" [Wikipedia:Medial_palpebral_arteries]\nsynonym: \"inferior palpebral artery\" RELATED [Wikipedia:Medial_palpebral_arteries]\nsynonym: \"internal palpebral arteries\" RELATED [Wikipedia:Medial_palpebral_arteries]\nsynonym: \"internal palpebral artery\" RELATED [Wikipedia:Medial_palpebral_arteries]\nsynonym: \"medial palpebral branch of ophthalmic artery\" EXACT [FMA:50012]\nsynonym: \"superior palpebral\" RELATED [Wikipedia:Medial_palpebral_arteries]\nsynonym: \"superior palpebral artery\" RELATED [Wikipedia:Medial_palpebral_arteries]\nxref: FMA:50012\nxref: SCTID:369331003\nxref: Wikipedia:Medial_palpebral_arteries\nis_a: UBERON:0014770 ! palpebral artery\nrelationship: connecting_branch_of UBERON:0001619 {source=\"FMA\"} ! ophthalmic artery\n\n[Term]\nid: UBERON:0015156\nname: terminal branch of ophthalmic artery\ndef: \"The two terminal branches of the ophthalmic artery in humans are the dorsal nasal artery and the supratrochlear artery.\" [Wikipedia:Dorsal_nasal_artery, Wikipedia:Supratrochlear_artery]\nxref: FMA:51956\nis_a: UBERON:0001637 ! artery\nrelationship: connecting_branch_of UBERON:0001619 ! ophthalmic artery\n\n[Term]\nid: UBERON:0015157\nname: zygomatico-orbital artery\ndef: \"The middle temporal artery occasionally gives off a zygomatico-orbital branch, which runs along the upper border of the zygomatic arch, between the two layers of the temporal fascia, to the lateral angle of the orbit. This branch, which may arise directly from the superficial temporal artery, supplies the Orbicularis oculi, and anastomoses with the lacrimal and palpebral branches of the ophthalmic artery.\" [Wikipedia:Zygomatico-orbital_artery]\nsynonym: \"zygomaticooerbital branch\" RELATED [Wikipedia:Zygomatico-orbital_artery]\nsynonym: \"zygomaticoorbital branch\" RELATED [Wikipedia:Zygomatico-orbital_artery]\nxref: FMA:49663\nxref: SCTID:146753008\nxref: Wikipedia:Zygomatico-orbital_artery\nis_a: UBERON:0001637 ! artery\nrelationship: connecting_branch_of UBERON:0001614 {source=\"FMA\"} ! superficial temporal artery\n\n[Term]\nid: UBERON:0015158\nname: ophthalmotemporal branch of external ophthalmic artery\ncomment: The blood supply to the (Harderian) gland has been reported in greatest detail in the sparrow Passer domesticus (Slonaker, 1918), where it is derived through the ophthalmotemporal branch of the external ophthalmic artery http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/7559104\nsynonym: \"ophthalmotemporal artery\" RELATED []\nis_a: UBERON:0001637 ! artery\nrelationship: connecting_branch_of UBERON:0001619 ! ophthalmic artery\nrelationship: vessel_supplies_blood_to UBERON:0004187 {source=\"PMID:7559104\"} ! Harderian gland\n\n[Term]\nid: UBERON:0015160\nname: supraorbital artery\ndef: \"The supraorbital artery is an artery of the head. It springs from the ophthalmic artery as that vessel is crossing over to the medial side of the optic nerve.\" [Wikipedia:Supraorbital_artery]\nsynonym: \"arteria supraorbitalis\" EXACT OMO:0003011 [Wikipedia:Supraorbital_artery]\nsynonym: \"supra-orbital artery\" EXACT [FMA:49973]\nsynonym: \"supraorbital artery\" EXACT [FMA:49973]\nsynonym: \"supraorbital branch of external ophthalmic artery\" RELATED []\nxref: FMA:49973\nxref: SCTID:369330002\nxref: Wikipedia:Supraorbital_artery\nis_a: UBERON:0001637 ! artery\nrelationship: connecting_branch_of UBERON:0001619 ! ophthalmic artery\nrelationship: vessel_supplies_blood_to UBERON:0001604 ! levator palpebrae superioris\nrelationship: vessel_supplies_blood_to UBERON:0005027 ! mucosa of frontal sinus\n\n[Term]\nid: UBERON:0015480\nname: proper hepatic artery\ndef: \"The hepatic artery proper (also proper hepatic artery), arises from the common hepatic artery and runs alongside the portal vein and the common bile duct to form the portal triad. The hepatic artery proper gives off a small supraduodenal artery to the duodenal bulb. Then the right gastric artery comes off and runs to the left along the lesser curvature of the stomach to meet the left gastric artery, which is a branch of the celiac trunk. It subsequently gives off the cystic artery, which feeds the gallbladder, before bifurcating into the right and left hepatic arteries. Of note, the right and left hepatic arteries may demonstrate variant anatomy. A replaced right hepatic artery may arise from the superior mesenteric artery (SMA) and a replaced left hepatic artery may arise from the left gastric artery.\" [Wikipedia:Hepatic_artery_proper]\nsynonym: \"hepatic artery proper\" EXACT [FMA:14772]\nsynonym: \"proper hepatic\" RELATED [Wikipedia:Hepatic_artery_proper]\nxref: EMAPA:37217 {source=\"MA:th\"}\nxref: FMA:14772\nxref: MA:0003095\nxref: SCTID:244262006\nxref: Wikipedia:Hepatic_artery_proper\nis_a: UBERON:0001193 {source=\"MA\"} ! hepatic artery\nrelationship: connecting_branch_of UBERON:0005436 {source=\"FMA\"} ! common hepatic artery\n\n[Term]\nid: UBERON:0018231\nname: labyrinthine artery\ndef: \"A long slender branch of the anterior inferior cerebellar artery (85%-100% cases) or basilar artery (<15% cases), arises from near the middle of the artery; it accompanies the vestibulocochlear nerve through the internal acoustic meatus, and is distributed to the internal ear.\" [Wikipedia:Labyrinthine_artery]\nsynonym: \"arteria auditiva interna\" EXACT OMO:0003011 [Wikipedia:Labyrinthine_artery]\nsynonym: \"arteria labyrinthi\" EXACT OMO:0003011 [Wikipedia:Labyrinthine_artery]\nsynonym: \"artery of inner ear\" BROAD [FMA:50548]\nsynonym: \"internal auditory artery\" EXACT [FMA:50548]\nxref: EMAPA:37093 {source=\"MA:th\"}\nxref: FMA:50548\nxref: NCIT:C32834\nxref: SCTID:148672009\nxref: Wikipedia:Labyrinthine_artery\nis_a: UBERON:0001637 ! artery\nrelationship: branching_part_of UBERON:0009689 {gci_relation=\"part_of\", gci_filler=\"NCBITaxon:9606\", cases=\"85-100%\", source=\"WP\"} ! anterior inferior cerebellar artery\nrelationship: connecting_branch_of UBERON:0001633 {gci_relation=\"part_of\", gci_filler=\"NCBITaxon:9606\", cases=\"15%\", source=\"WP\"} ! basilar artery\nrelationship: part_of UBERON:0001846 ! internal ear\n\n[Term]\nid: UBERON:0018243\nname: thymic artery\ndef: \"A vein that supplies blood to the thymus.\" [http://orcid.org/0000-0002-6601-2165]\ncomment: The arteries supplying the thymus are derived from the internal thoracic artery, and from the superior thyroid artery and inferior thyroids.[WP]\nsynonym: \"thymic arteries\" RELATED OMO:0003004 [Wikipedia:Thymic_branches_of_internal_thoracic_artery]\nsynonym: \"thymic branch of internal thoracic artery\" EXACT [FMA:10647]\nxref: FMA:10647\nxref: SCTID:76543001\nxref: Wikipedia:Thymic_branches_of_internal_thoracic_artery\nintersection_of: UBERON:0001637 ! artery\nintersection_of: vessel_supplies_blood_to UBERON:0002370 ! thymus\nrelationship: connecting_branch_of UBERON:0002456 {source=\"FMA\"} ! internal thoracic artery\n\n[Term]\nid: UBERON:0018250\nname: middle thyroid artery\nis_a: UBERON:0003847 ! thyroid artery\nrelationship: connecting_branch_of UBERON:0001070 {source=\"PMC1167197\"} ! external carotid artery\nproperty_value: taxon_notes \"In Cavio cobaya, arises from the external carotid or distal half of the common carotid artery, passed the thyroid gland cranially or penetrated it to terminate in the inferior laryngeal artery\" xsd:string\n\n[Term]\nid: UBERON:0018397\nname: posterior superior alveolar artery\ndef: \"The posterior superior alveolar artery (posterior dental artery) is given off from the maxillary, frequently in conjunction with the infraorbital just as the trunk of the vessel is passing into the pterygopalatine fossa.\" [Wikipedia:Posterior_superior_alveolar_artery]\nsynonym: \"superior posterior alveolar artery\" EXACT [FMA:49757]\nxref: FMA:49757\nxref: Wikipedia:Posterior_superior_alveolar_artery\nis_a: UBERON:0001637 ! artery\nrelationship: connecting_branch_of UBERON:0001616 {source=\"FMA\"} ! maxillary artery\n\n[Term]\nid: UBERON:0034693\nname: cremasteric artery\ndef: \"The cremasteric artery (external spermatic artery) is a branch of the Inferior epigastric artery which accompanies the spermatic cord, and supplies the Cremaster and other coverings of the cord, anastomosing with the testicular artery (internal spermatic artery in older texts). (In the female, the cremesteric artery is very small and accompanies the round ligament.).\" [Wikipedia:Cremasteric_artery]\nsynonym: \"cremasteric part of inferior epigastric artery\" EXACT [FMA:70192]\nsynonym: \"external spermatic artery\" RELATED [Wikipedia:Cremasteric_artery]\nxref: FMA:70192\nxref: SCTID:279658002\nxref: Wikipedia:Cremasteric_artery\nis_a: UBERON:0001637 ! artery\nrelationship: connecting_branch_of UBERON:0001354 {source=\"FMA\"} ! inferior epigastric artery\nrelationship: part_of UBERON:0001354 {source=\"FMA\"} ! inferior epigastric artery\n\n[Term]\nid: UBERON:0034727\nname: vestibular bulb artery\ndef: \"The artery of bulb of vestibule is a branch of the internal pudendal artery.\" [Wikipedia:Artery_of_bulb_of_vestibule]\nsynonym: \"arteria bulbi vestibuli\" EXACT OMO:0003011 [FMA:TA]\nsynonym: \"artery of bulb of vestibule\" EXACT [FMA:20900]\nxref: FMA:20900\nxref: SCTID:293541004\nxref: Wikipedia:Artery_of_bulb_of_vestibule\nintersection_of: UBERON:0001637 ! artery\nintersection_of: vessel_supplies_blood_to UBERON:0013129 ! bulb of vestibule\nrelationship: connecting_branch_of UBERON:0007315 {source=\"FMA\"} ! internal pudendal artery\n\n[Term]\nid: UBERON:0034927\nname: arcuate artery of foot\ndef: \"The arcuate artery of the foot (metatarsal artery) arises a little anterior to the lateral tarsal artery; it passes lateralward, over the bases of the metatarsal bones, beneath the tendons of the Extensor digitorum brevis, its direction being influenced by its point of origin; and its anastomoses with the lateral tarsal and lateral plantar arteries. This vessel gives off the second, third, and fourth dorsal metatarsal arteries. It is not present in all individuals.\" [Wikipedia:Arcuate_artery_of_the_foot]\nxref: FMA:44594\nxref: SCTID:244331005\nxref: Wikipedia:Arcuate_artery_of_the_foot\nis_a: UBERON:0001637 ! artery\nrelationship: connecting_branch_of UBERON:0001537 {source=\"FMA\"} ! anterior tibial artery\nrelationship: part_of UBERON:0002387 ! pes\n\n[Term]\nid: UBERON:0035040\nname: superior rectal artery\ndef: \"The superior rectal artery (superior hemorrhoidal artery) is an artery that descends into the pelvis to supply blood to the rectum.\" [Wikipedia:Superior_rectal_artery]\nsynonym: \"superior hemorrhoidal\" RELATED [Wikipedia:Superior_rectal_artery]\nsynonym: \"superior hemorrhoidal artery\" EXACT [FMA:14832]\nsynonym: \"superior hemorrhoidal artery\" RELATED [Wikipedia:Superior_rectal_artery]\nsynonym: \"superior rectal\" RELATED [Wikipedia:Superior_rectal_artery]\nxref: FMA:14832\nxref: NCIT:C33677\nxref: SCTID:244278008\nxref: Wikipedia:Superior_rectal_artery\nis_a: UBERON:0035039 ! rectal artery\nrelationship: connecting_branch_of UBERON:0001183 {source=\"FMA\"} ! inferior mesenteric artery\nrelationship: part_of UBERON:0001183 {source=\"FMA\"} ! inferior mesenteric artery\n\n[Term]\nid: UBERON:0035041\nname: deep temporal artery\ndef: \"The deep temporal arteries, two in number, anterior and posterior, ascend between the Temporalis and the pericranium. They supply the muscle, and anastomose with the middle temporal artery. The anterior communicates with the lacrimal artery by means of small branches which perforate the zygomatic bone and great wing of the sphenoid.\" [Wikipedia:Deep_temporal_arteries]\nsynonym: \"anterior deep temporal artery\" RELATED [Wikipedia:Deep_temporal_arteries]\nsynonym: \"deep temporal arteries\" RELATED [Wikipedia:Deep_temporal_arteries]\nsynonym: \"deep temporal artery\" RELATED [Wikipedia:Deep_temporal_arteries]\nsynonym: \"deep temporal branches\" RELATED [Wikipedia:Deep_temporal_arteries]\nsynonym: \"posterior deep temporal artery\" RELATED [Wikipedia:Deep_temporal_arteries]\nxref: FMA:49742\nxref: SCTID:147965009\nxref: Wikipedia:Deep_temporal_arteries\nintersection_of: UBERON:0001632 ! temporal artery\nintersection_of: part_of UBERON:0035551 ! deep vasculature\nrelationship: connecting_branch_of UBERON:0001616 {source=\"FMA\"} ! maxillary artery\n\n[Term]\nid: UBERON:0035042\nname: middle temporal artery\ndef: \"The middle temporal artery arises immediately above the zygomatic arch, and, perforating the temporal fascia, gives branches to the Temporalis, anastomosing with the deep temporal branches of the internal maxillary. It occasionally gives off a zygomaticoC6rbital branch, which runs along the upper border of the zygomatic arch, between the two layers of the temporal fascia, to the lateral angle of the orbit.\" [Wikipedia:Middle_temporal_artery]\nsynonym: \"middle temporal artery\" RELATED [Wikipedia:Middle_temporal_artery]\nxref: FMA:49666\nxref: SCTID:146854006\nxref: Wikipedia:Middle_temporal_artery\nis_a: UBERON:0001632 ! temporal artery\nrelationship: connecting_branch_of UBERON:0001614 {source=\"FMA\"} ! superficial temporal artery\n\n[Term]\nid: UBERON:0035180\nname: sigmoid artery\ndef: \"The sigmoid arteries, two or three in number, run obliquely downward and to the left behind the peritoneum and in front of the Psoas major, ureter, and internal spermatic vessels. Their branches supply the lower part of the descending colon, the iliac colon, and the sigmoid or pelvic colon; anastomosing above with the left colic, and below with the superior hemorrhoidal artery.\" [Wikipedia:Sigmoid_arteries]\nsynonym: \"inferior left colic artery\" EXACT [FMA:14830]\nxref: FMA:14830\nxref: NCIT:C33549\nxref: SCTID:265956005\nxref: UMLS:C0226330\nxref: Wikipedia:Sigmoid_arteries\nis_a: UBERON:0001637 ! artery\nrelationship: connecting_branch_of UBERON:0001183 {source=\"FMA\"} ! inferior mesenteric artery\n\n[Term]\nid: UBERON:0035222\nname: posterior parietal artery\nxref: FMA:50488\nxref: NCIT:C33372\nxref: SCTID:44894007\nxref: UMLS:C0226227\nis_a: UBERON:0001637 ! artery\ndisjoint_from: UBERON:0035462 {source=\"lexical\"} ! anterior parietal artery\nrelationship: connecting_branch_of UBERON:0001627 {source=\"FMA\"} ! middle cerebral artery\n\n[Term]\nid: UBERON:0035225\nname: anterior temporal artery\ndef: \"A branch of the middle cerebral artery that supplies blood to the anterior part of the temporal lobe.\" [ncithesaurus:Anterior_Temporal_Artery]\nxref: FMA:50382\nxref: NCIT:C32113\nxref: SCTID:44310009\nxref: UMLS:C0226228\nis_a: UBERON:0001632 {source=\"FMA\"} ! temporal artery\ndisjoint_from: UBERON:0035261 {source=\"lexical\"} ! posterior temporal artery\nrelationship: connecting_branch_of UBERON:0001627 {source=\"FMA\"} ! middle cerebral artery\n\n[Term]\nid: UBERON:0035261\nname: posterior temporal artery\nxref: FMA:50458\nxref: NCIT:C33384\nxref: SCTID:23830002\nxref: UMLS:C0226229\nis_a: UBERON:0001632 {source=\"FMA\"} ! temporal artery\nrelationship: connecting_branch_of UBERON:0001627 {source=\"FMA\"} ! middle cerebral artery\n\n[Term]\nid: UBERON:0035273\nname: superior thoracic artery\ndef: \"The superior thoracic artery (highest thoracic artery) is a small vessel normally arising from the first division of the axillary artery, but may arise from the thoracoacromial artery, itself a branch of the second division of the axillary artery. Running forward and medialward along the upper border of the pectoralis minor, the superior thoracic artery passes between it and the pectoralis major to the side of the chest. It supplies branches to the first and second intercostal spaces as well as to the superior portion of serratus anterior. It anastomoses with the internal mammary and intercostal arteries.\" [Wikipedia:Superior_thoracic_artery]\nxref: FMA:22668\nxref: NCIT:C33701\nxref: SCTID:198713000\nxref: UMLS:C0226419\nxref: Wikipedia:Superior_thoracic_artery\nis_a: UBERON:0001637 ! artery\nrelationship: connecting_branch_of UBERON:0001394 {source=\"FMA\"} ! axillary artery\n\n[Term]\nid: UBERON:0035404\nname: superior hypophysial artery\ndef: \"The superior hypophysial artery is an artery supplying the pars tuberalis,the infundibulum of the pituitary gland and the median eminence. It is a branch of the posterior communicating artery which branches from the internal carotid artery in the circle of Willis..\" [Wikipedia:Superior_hypophysial_artery]\nsynonym: \"superior hypophyseal artery\" EXACT [FMA:49849]\nxref: FMA:49849\nxref: NCIT:C33678\nxref: SCTID:303427008\nxref: UMLS:C1261387\nxref: Wikipedia:Superior_hypophysial_artery\nis_a: UBERON:0001637 ! artery\nrelationship: connecting_branch_of UBERON:0001532 ! internal carotid artery\nrelationship: vessel_supplies_blood_to UBERON:0000007 ! pituitary gland\n\n[Term]\nid: UBERON:0035422\nname: circumflex branch of left coronary artery\ndef: \"Branch of left coronary artery which runs perpendicular to the anterior interventricular branch of the left coronary artery on the left side of the interventricular sulcus and supplies the left side of the heart.\" [FMA:3895]\nsynonym: \"circumflex coronary artery\" EXACT [FMA:3895]\nsynonym: \"left circumflex branch of left coronary artery\" EXACT [FMA:3895]\nsynonym: \"ramus circumflexus (arteria coronaria sinistra)\" EXACT OMO:0003011 [FMA:3895, FMA:TA]\nxref: FMA:3895\nxref: NCIT:C12874\nxref: SCTID:362036002\nxref: UMLS:C0226037\nxref: Wikipedia:Circumflex_branch_of_left_coronary_artery\nis_a: UBERON:0001637 ! artery\nrelationship: connecting_branch_of UBERON:0001626 {source=\"FMA\"} ! left coronary artery\nrelationship: part_of UBERON:0001626 {source=\"FMA\"} ! left coronary artery\n\n[Term]\nid: UBERON:0035462\nname: anterior parietal artery\ndef: \"The artery that delivers blood to the anterior portion of the parietal lobe.\" [ncithesaurus:Anterior_Parietal_Artery]\nxref: FMA:50485\nxref: NCIT:C32101\nxref: SCTID:78499006\nxref: UMLS:C0226226\nis_a: UBERON:0001637 ! artery\nrelationship: connecting_branch_of UBERON:0001627 {source=\"FMA\"} ! middle cerebral artery\n\n[Term]\nid: UBERON:0035492\nname: inferior hypophysial artery\ndef: \"The inferior hypophysial artery is an artery supplying the pituitary gland. It is a branch of the cavernous carotid artery (internal carotid artery).\" [Wikipedia:Inferior_hypophysial_artery]\nsynonym: \"inferior hypophyseal artery\" EXACT [FMA:49846]\nxref: FMA:49846\nxref: NCIT:C32777\nxref: SCTID:303428003\nxref: UMLS:C1261083\nxref: Wikipedia:Inferior_hypophysial_artery\nis_a: UBERON:0001637 ! artery\nrelationship: connecting_branch_of UBERON:0001532 ! internal carotid artery\nrelationship: vessel_supplies_blood_to UBERON:0000007 ! pituitary gland\n\n[Term]\nid: UBERON:0035829\nname: right gastroepiploic artery\ndef: \"Artery that runs from right to left along the greater curvature of the stomach, between the layers of the greater omentum, anastomosing with the left gastroepiploic branch of the splenic artery.\" [Wikipedia:Right_gastro-omental_artery]\nsynonym: \"arteria gastro-omentalis dextra\" EXACT OMO:0003011 [Wikipedia:Right_gastro-omental_artery]\nsynonym: \"arteria gastroepiploica dextra\" EXACT OMO:0003011 [Wikipedia:Right_gastro-omental_artery]\nsynonym: \"arteria gastroomentalis dextra\" EXACT OMO:0003011 [Wikipedia:Right_gastro-omental_artery]\nsynonym: \"right gastro-epiploic artery\" EXACT [FMA:14781]\nsynonym: \"right gastro-omental artery\" EXACT [FMA:14781]\nsynonym: \"right gastroepiploic\" RELATED [Wikipedia:Right_gastro-omental_artery]\nsynonym: \"right gastroepiploic artery\" RELATED [Wikipedia:Right_gastro-omental_artery]\nsynonym: \"right gastroomental artery\" EXACT [FMA:14781]\nxref: FMA:14781\nxref: SCTID:244271002\nxref: Wikipedia:Right_gastro-omental_artery\nis_a: UBERON:0009025 ! gastroepiploic artery\nrelationship: connecting_branch_of UBERON:0010132 {source=\"FMA\"} ! gastroduodenal artery\nrelationship: vessel_supplies_blood_to UBERON:0002108 {source=\"FMA\"} ! small intestine\n\n[Term]\nid: UBERON:0035830\nname: left gastroepiploic artery\ndef: \"Artery that runs from left to right along the greater curvature of the stomach, between the layers of the greater omentum, and anastomoses with the right gastroepiploic.\" [Wikipedia:Left_gastro-omental_artery]\nsynonym: \"arteria gastro-omentalis sinistra\" EXACT OMO:0003011 [Wikipedia:Left_gastro-omental_artery]\nsynonym: \"arteria gastroepiploica sinistra\" EXACT OMO:0003011 [Wikipedia:Left_gastro-omental_artery]\nsynonym: \"arteria gastroomentalis sinistra\" EXACT OMO:0003011 [Wikipedia:Left_gastro-omental_artery]\nsynonym: \"left gastro-epiploic artery\" EXACT [FMA:14796]\nsynonym: \"left gastro-omental artery\" EXACT [FMA:14796]\nsynonym: \"left gastroepiploic artery\" RELATED [Wikipedia:Left_gastro-omental_artery]\nsynonym: \"left gastroepiploic branch\" RELATED [Wikipedia:Left_gastro-omental_artery]\nsynonym: \"left gastroomental artery\" EXACT [FMA:14796]\nsynonym: \"left inferior gastric artery\" EXACT [FMA:14796]\nxref: FMA:14796\nxref: SCTID:244270001\nxref: Wikipedia:Left_gastro-omental_artery\nis_a: UBERON:0009025 ! gastroepiploic artery\nrelationship: connecting_branch_of UBERON:0001194 {source=\"FMA\"} ! splenic artery\n\n[Term]\nid: UBERON:0039215\nname: appendicular artery\ndef: \"An artery that commonly arises from the terminal branch of the ileocolic artery, or less commonly from the posterior cecal artery or an ileal artery.[1][2] It descends behind the termination of the ileum and enters the mesoappendix of the vermiform appendix. It runs near the free margin of the mesoappendix and ends in branches which supply the appendix.\" [https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Appendicular_artery]\nsynonym: \"appendiceal artery\" EXACT [FMA:14818]\nxref: FMA:14818\nis_a: UBERON:0001637 ! artery\nrelationship: connecting_branch_of UBERON:0001197 ! ileocolic artery\nrelationship: vessel_supplies_blood_to UBERON:0001154 {source=\"FMA\"} ! vermiform appendix\n\n[Term]\nid: UBERON:0039261\nname: pancreatic artery\nxref: FMA:70471\nintersection_of: UBERON:0001637 ! artery\nintersection_of: vessel_supplies_blood_to UBERON:0001264 ! pancreas\nrelationship: connecting_branch_of UBERON:0001194 ! splenic artery\n\n[Term]\nid: UBERON:0039351\nname: posterior labial artery\nsynonym: \"posterior labial branch of internal pudendal artery\" EXACT [FMA:20886]\nxref: FMA:20886\nis_a: UBERON:0001637 ! artery\nrelationship: connecting_branch_of UBERON:0001358 {source=\"FMA\"} ! perineal artery\n\n[Term]\nid: UBERON:8410022\nname: left colic artery\ndef: \"The first branch of the inferior mesenteric artery (IMA) is the left colic artery. The left colic artery supplies blood flow to the distal third of the transverse colon and the entirety of the descending colon. Once diverging from the IMA, the left colic artery runs anterior to the left ureter, left internal spermatic vessels (males), and psoas major before branching into its ascending and descending segments.\" [https://orcid.org/0000-0003-4183-8865, PMID:29489246]\nxref: FMA:14826\nis_a: UBERON:0001637 ! artery\nrelationship: connecting_branch_of UBERON:0001183 ! inferior mesenteric artery\nrelationship: dc-contributor https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2825-0621 ! Paola Roncaglia\nrelationship: vessel_supplies_blood_to UBERON:0001157 ! transverse colon\nrelationship: vessel_supplies_blood_to UBERON:0001158 ! descending colon\n\n[Term]\nid: UBERON:8410035\nname: medullary arteriole of lymph node\ndef: \"An arteriole that arises from the hilar artery of a lymph node and radiates centrifugally, branching in the medulla.\" [http://orcid.org/0000-0003-3440-1876, PMID:17067937]\nsynonym: \"arteriole of medulla of lymph node\" EXACT []\nintersection_of: UBERON:0001980 ! arteriole\nintersection_of: part_of UBERON:0002007 ! medulla of lymph node\nrelationship: connecting_branch_of UBERON:8410034 ! lymph node artery\nrelationship: dc-contributor https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2825-0621 ! Paola Roncaglia\n\n","exit":0,"description":"Check if 'connecting_branch_of' is used in the ontology with the correct flag.","truncated":true,"outputPath":"/home/runner/.local/share/opencode/tool-output/tool_e19a69929001ai76mGQF2cOHCN"},"title":"Check if 'connecting_branch_of' is used in the ontology with the correct flag.","time":{"start":1778546809137,"end":1778546809142}},"id":"prt_e19a69451001wLSynHxdxIkldl","sessionID":"ses_1e65d1530ffeDUY9bNFKPZlPsk","messageID":"msg_e19a614a0001lMq2DXwgxE93c3"}}
